text: Heosphora psamathella is a moth in the family Pyralidae. The species was first described by Edward Meyrick in 1879, as Anerastia psamathella, from a male specimen collected in Sydney, New South Wales, and was moved to the genus Heosphora as its type species by George Hampson in 1901. It is found in Australia. == References == Category:Moths described in 1879 Category:Moths of Australia Category:Taxa named by Edward Meyrick
title: Heosphora psamathella
